CRIJ 5340 - Violence and Society
A review of the causes, treatment and impact of violent behavior,
particularly serial/chronic violence in American society. Domestic
violence is included in the review. Biological, psychological and
sociological causes will be analyzed and compared. Responses by the
Criminal Justice System, the public, the media, health care system, etc.
will be analyzed. Impact on and treatment for victims, both adults and
children, will be included.
